Oxybutynin, also marketed as Ditropan XL, is an anticholinergic medication used for the relief of overactive bladder symptoms that has been optimized for high levels of safety and efficacy since initial FDA approval in 1975.[A183782,L8648] This drug relieves undesirable urinary symptoms, increasing the quality of life for patients affected by OAB.  It is often used as first-line therapy for OAB.[A185990]', '["G04BD04"]', '[]');
